Amanda Khoza, News24New eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede. (Amanda Khoza, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; Zandile Gumede was elected as the new eThekwini Metro mayor on Tuesday, taking over the reins from James Nxumalo.&nbsp;She is the metro&rsquo;s first female mayor.&nbsp;Gumede received 124 votes. The DA&rsquo;s candidate Zwakele Mncwango got 87.ANC councillors erupted into song when Gumede&rsquo;s name was announced, singing the party&rsquo;s anthem, Asinavalo (We are not afraid).&nbsp;Before the nomination, the DA made a surprise announcement that it had nominated Mncwango and ditched Haniff Hoosen who had been the party&rsquo;s face in the metro for the August 3 municipal elections.&nbsp;Minority Front councillor Patrick Pillay objected to the sudden change. Newly-elected speaker Lekgoa Mapena dismissed his objection.&nbsp;It was not immediately clear why the DA chose Mncwango over Hoosen.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.